subSubSection.paragraph:
In addition to seeps, 

Nucinella

can be found in a range of other shallow to deep marine modern environments (
Allen & Sanders 1969
; 

Matsukuma 
et al.
1982

; 
Okutani & Iwasaki 2003
; 
La Perna 2004
), including organic-rich sediments in fjords (

McLeod 
et al.
2010

), and at oxygen-minimum zones (
Oliver & Taylor 2012
). As a fossil it occurs in a range of post-Triassic marine deposits (i.e. 
Wood 1851
; 
Bistram 1903
; 
Vokes 1956
; 
Clausen & Wignall 1990
; 

Studencka 
et al.
1998

; 
Harries & Little 1999
; 
Schneider 2008
).
